Session 17: Web Server Hacking, Web Vulns, Wireless Hacking & Wireless Security
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Hacking a web server mainly aims to:
A. Improve performance
B. Gain unauthorized control
C. Backup data
D. Monitor traffic

2. Web application vulnerabilities mostly arise due to:
A. Hardware failure
B. Poor coding and configuration
C. Power issues
D. ISP problems

3. Which is a common web application vulnerability?
A. SQL Injection
B. Power outage
C. Disk failure
D. Cable cut

4. Web-based password cracking targets:
A. Network devices
B. Authentication mechanisms
C. Hardware BIOS
D. DNS server

5. Wireless hacking targets which medium?
A. Optical fiber
B. Copper cable
C. Airwaves
D. USB

6. WEP stands for:
A. Wired Equivalent Privacy
B. Wireless Encrypted Protocol
C. Wide Encryption Policy
D. Web Encryption Process

7. WPA is more secure than WEP because it uses:
A. Static keys
B. Dynamic key management
C. Plain text
D. No encryption

8. Wireless sniffing is used to:
A. Encrypt traffic
B. Capture wireless packets
C. Block signals
D. Authenticate users

9. MAC spoofing means:
A. Encrypting MAC
B. Changing MAC address
C. Blocking MAC
D. Learning MAC

10. Securing wireless networks mainly protects:
A. Confidentiality
B. Availability
C. Performance
D. Speed

